article.description: Heather Ezell led Iowa State past IPFW on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Ezell leads Iowa State past IPFW
article.linkText: Ezell, No. 25 Iowa State run winning streak to 7
article.story:
Heather Ezell scored 19 points as Iowa State (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today) routed IPFW on Wednesday to run its winning streak to seven games.

Alison Lacey added 16 points and 11 rebounds for the Cyclones (12-2) who finished off the non-conference portion of their schedule.

Sarah Haluska came off the bench to lead the Mastadons (2-12) with 13 points.
